Package ohos.biometrics.authentication

Class BiometricAuthentication

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.biometrics.authentication.BiometricAuthentication

  • public class BiometricAuthentication
extends Object
    Provides the biometric authentication capability.

    This class provides methods for checking the biometric authentication capability, and performing and canceling authentication.

    Since:
    1
    SystemCapability
    SystemCapability.useriam.userauth.biometric_auth

      • checkAuthenticationAvailability

        public int checkAuthenticationAvailability​(BiometricAuthentication.AuthType type,
                                           BiometricAuthentication.SecureLevel level,
                                           boolean isLocalAuth)
        Checks whether a device supports biometric authentication.

        This method is used to check whether the device supports biometric authentication based on AuthType, SecureLevel, and isLocalAuth. If biometric authentication is not supported, consider using other authentication capabilities.

        Parameters:
        type - Indicates the authentication type, which is specified by AuthType.
        level - Indicates the security level, which is specified by SecureLevel.
        isLocalAuth - Indicates whether local authentication is used. Value false indicates distributed authentication. Currently, only local authentication is supported.
        Returns:
        Returns BA_CHECK_SUPPORTED if the device supports biometric authentication. Other return values can be referenced by BA_CHECK_AUTH_TYPE_NOT_SUPPORT, BA_CHECK_SECURE_LEVEL_NOT_SUPPORT, BA_CHECK_DISTRIBUTED_AUTH_NOT_SUPPORT, BA_CHECK_NOT_ENROLLED, BA_CHECK_UNAVAILABLE, BA_FAILED.
        Since:
        1

      • execAuthenticationAction

        public int execAuthenticationAction​(BiometricAuthentication.AuthType type,
                                    BiometricAuthentication.SecureLevel level,
                                    boolean isLocalAuth,
                                    boolean isAppAuthDialog,
                                    BiometricAuthentication.SystemAuthDialogInfo information)
        Performs biometric authentication.

        You can use either the system-provided or a customized authentication dialog box. If you use the former, you can customize the authentication tips. The authentication result is returned only after the authentication is complete. To cancel the authentication, use cancelAuthenticationAction().

        Parameters:
        type - Indicates the authentication type, which is specified by AuthType.
        level - Indicates the security level, which is specified by SecureLevel.
        isLocalAuth - Indicates whether local authentication is used. Value false indicates distributed authentication. Currently, only local authentication is supported.
        isAppAuthDialog - Indicates whether a customized authentication dialog box is used.
        information - Indicates the authentication tips in the system-provided authentication dialog box.
        Returns:
        Returns the result code in IFaceAuthentication.FaceAuthResultCode.
        Since:
        1

      • getAuthenticationTips

        public BiometricAuthentication.AuthenticationTips getAuthenticationTips​()
        Obtains authentication tips.

        An example is the tip to adjust the face angle in face recognition.

        Returns:
        Returns authentication tips, which are specified by AuthenticationTips.
        Since:
        1

      • cancelAuthenticationAction

        public int cancelAuthenticationAction​()
        Cancels biometric authentication.

        Performing and canceling an authentication must be in different threads and have the same identifier. This method is used to cancel an ongoing biometric authentication.

        Returns:
        Returns BA_SUCCESS if the authentication is canceled; returns BA_FAILED otherwise.
        Since:
        1

      • setSecureObjectSignature

        public void setSecureObjectSignature​(Signature sign)
        Sets the Signature object associated with the authentication result.

        If an authentication succeeds, the Signature object associated with the authentication result is authorized and available. The Signature object must be initialized correctly before it is associated with the authentication result.

        Parameters:
        sign - Indicates the Signature object to be associated with the authentication result.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Throws this exception if the input parameter is not a Signature object.
        IllegalStateException - Throws this exception if the private key of the input parameter is not correctly initialized.
        Since:
        1

      • getSecureObjectSignature
